# File: specs/bug-fix-run-loop-child-codex-github-access/feature.gherkin
#
# Generated from: specs/bug-fix-run-loop-child-codex-github-access/requirements.md
# Issue: #122
# Type: Defect regression

@regression @run-loop @issue-122
Feature: Runner-spawned child Codex sessions are not sandboxed
  The SDLC runner previously launched every child Codex step with sandboxed
  --full-auto execution. GitHub-dependent child sessions could not reach
  api.github.com even when the parent runner process had GitHub access.

  @regression
  Scenario: All runner-spawned child steps use yolo execution
    Given the SDLC runner has configured pipeline steps
    When the runner builds codex exec arguments for each step
    Then every child command includes the yolo no-sandbox flag
    And no child command includes the sandboxed full-auto flag

  @regression
  Scenario: GitHub-dependent child steps have GitHub access
    Given the parent runner process can run a read-only gh issue command
    When a runner-spawned child Codex session runs the same GitHub-dependent command
    Then the child command is launched without Codex sandboxing
    And the GitHub command is not blocked by api.github.com sandbox restrictions

  @regression
  Scenario: startIssue escalates known GitHub access failures immediately
    Given Step 2 startIssue exits with code 0
    And the child output contains "error connecting to api.github.com"
    When the runner classifies the child result
    Then the result is treated as a GitHub access soft failure
    And the concrete GitHub access failure is surfaced before no-branch retries are exhausted

  @regression
  Scenario: Missing feature branch still catches silent startIssue failures
    Given Step 2 startIssue exits with code 0
    And the child output does not contain a GitHub auth or network failure
    When no feature branch is checked out after the child session completes
    Then the missing-feature-branch postcondition treats the step as a soft failure
    And the runner routes through the normal retry or escalation path

  @regression
  Scenario: Parent and child capability parity is verified
    Given the parent runner process can perform a representative SDLC capability operation
    When the runner child launch mode is exercised for the same operation
    Then the child session can perform the operation with equivalent capability
    And verification fails with a capability-divergence diagnostic if the child remains sandboxed
